  "texts": [
    "• Knowledge Completeness of Retrieved Documents: They evaluated whether the retrieved documents contained sufficient information to answer the question (can/cannot).",
    "Based on these assessments, we used a voting mechanism among the annotators to categorize each question into one of the four types outlined in Section 3.2.",
    "In the actual reasoning phase, the categorization is supported by the evaluator LLM and NLI model.",
    "The evaluator LLM assesses the internal knowledge (i.e., the LLM's own understanding and the quality of its closebook answer), while the NLI model evaluates the external knowledge.",
    "This dual evaluation helps determine whether the LLM has the necessary internal knowledge and whether the external information is adequate to formulate a correct response."
